Horrible service. I order my food via Uber Eats and upon completion of my ordered I was prompted that the store would be executing the delivery of the food.  I called the store to follow up and they informed me that Uber would be delivering the food. I informed them of what the uber eats app relayed to me and was directed to the manager. She first said the same thing I was initially told. When I explained to her that the app stated the store would be taking care of the order she then stated that the food was on its way. After 30 minutes I checked back with the store and the young woman who answered said she would call the driver and check on the order and then call me back. She called back from a different number than the one listed as the business line and said that I should call uber because she does not know where the driver is and they don't deliver food. I referred again to the fact that the app has only given me a message stating that the store would deliver the food and I would not be able to track a driver. The young lady then put me on hold and left me on hold without returning. I disconnected and attempted to call the store twice and there was no answer. Then called the other number and the manager answered aggitated saying that there was nothing she could do. I then proceeded to ask her for the contact information of the driver that they had on my ticket and she said she did not have any info and that the younglady was new. I recited to her what the young lady said about having the drivers' contact info and it became a yelling match where she disconnected the call. The service here is horrible. Apparently their ordering system on the app is faulty and leaves customers misinformed and left with bad attitude and incompetence to make up for it. I will never forget this experience and the behavior exhibited was unbecoming of management.
